Water level appears to be down about 3" to 4".

Sunny- wind from the SW at 5 to 10 mph- air temp 88 degrees- water temp 82 degrees- no boats on the lake.  We consistently get a Secchi disk depth around 9.0 feet this year.  We used a GPS to find a deep spot early this year and use the GPS to consistently get back to the same spot.

Partly cloudy- wind from the NE from 5 to 10 mph- air temp 77 degrees- water temp 78 degrees- no boats on the lake.  The lake level is down about 6".  I checked the measurement marks on the Secchi disk rope and found that the 10' mark was actually 10' 4".  I recalibrated and remarked all the marks on the rope from the 5' mark to the 10' mark.  Today's measurement is based on the new- correct marks.  That probably means that this year's earlier Secchi disk measurements should be increased by just over 3".

The lake is about 4" to 5" lower today- at the end of August- than it was for our first 2008 Secchi disk reading at the end of May.

Received current year forms- material and new digital thermometer from Kris Larsen- so we did the chemical testing and thermometer reading for June- but did not do a Secchi disk since we had just done one on 7/8.

Clear- wind 15 to 20 mph from the west- air temp 72 degrees- water temp 74 degrees- no boats on the lake- water was clear at the surface but appeared brownish at deeper levels making it harder to see the Secchi disk as it got deeper; high water level = 3" to 4" higher than normal because of a hard rain on 7/27 in the evening.

Mostly cloudy- wind 15 to 20 mph from the NW- air temp 75 degrees- water temp 77 degrees- no boats on the lake- water was clear but appeared brownish at deeper levels.  With the Secchi disk at one to two feet- the water is like clear glass- but when the Secchi disk drops below four feet- the water seems to start turning a brownish color and becomes harder to see at the deeper levels.  .

Mostly clear- wind 20 to 25 mph from the West- air temp 72 degrees- water temp 77 degrees- no boats on the lake- water level on the lake is about 3" to 4" high from the recent rainfall- water at the top is clear but about 2' it starts to turn brownish in color like iron colored or tamarack colored water.

Cloudy- NW wind 15 mph- air temp 56 degrees- water temp 58 degrees- no boats on the lake- one swan on the lake.  The swan has been around on the lake for the past five days.  The previous four days had strong winds (20 to 30 mph) first out of the south- then out of the NW.  This stirred up the lake so there may still be some floating particles in the water from the strong winds.

Mostly cloudy- wind 15 mph from the NE- air temp 73 degrees- water temp 73 degrees- no boats on the lake.  In the last week- we had several storms  with lots of rain (one storm with 9") and strong winds (gusts to 50 mph) that stirred up the lake so there was lots of sediment suspended in the water making the water murky and brownish in color.

Mostly sunny- wind 5 to 10 mph from the North- air temp 75 degrees- water temp 76 degrees- no boats on the lake- we had rain and strong wind in the last few days that stirred up the lake and caused sediment floating in the water.
Sunny wind NE 5mph 75 degrees 1 boat 2 swans that appear to be nesting and loons on nest
mostly cloudy wind 5 mph NW 72 degrees no boats loon on nest 2 swans in same area they have been hanging out for about 6 weeks. Additional helpers Norah and Ryder Crow- Cindy Patza.

Sunny- West wind 5 mph- air temp 80 degrees- no other boats on the lake- two paddle boarders on the lake- one deer in the water on the west shoreline.  The air temp for the last week has been 80 degrees or above.

Mostly cloudy- light breeze from the north- two boats on the lake- water temp 76 degrees- air temp 70 degrees.

Mostly cloudy- light breeze from the south- no boats on the lake- water temp 72 degrees- air temp 71 degrees.  This year there are more lily pads and weed beds in the lake.  Have had some strong winds the last few days so the winds may have stirred up the silt in the water.  Have also had more warm days- a number in the 90's- so that could have made the lake water warmer.
Mostly cloudy- light breeze from the south- no boats on the lake- water temp 72 degrees- air temp 72 degrees- still more lily pads and weed beds than in past years.
